# Images

## Two asset types

| Type | Location | Render with |
|------|----------|-------------|
| **Raster** (JPG, PNG, WebP) | `public/images/<category>/` | `<Figure />` |
| **Decorative SVG** (icons, spots, rails) | `src/assets/crayon/` | `<CrayonArt />` |

Do **not** use raw `<img>` in app UI or MDX. Exception: third-party embeds encapsulated in `<YouTubeEmbed />`.

## Path convention

All raster URLs: `/images/<category>/<kebab-name>.<ext>`

| Category | Use |
|----------|-----|
| `deep-dives/` | Article reference photos |
| `life-cycles/` | Visualizer reference photos |
| `team/` | Author avatars |
| `brand/` | Logos, PWA sources (optional) |

In TypeScript, prefer `imagePath('life-cycles', 'eagle-nest.jpg')` or `images.team.author` from `src/lib/images.ts`.

## `<Figure />` variants

```tsx
import { Figure } from '../../components/content'

// Articles (default)
<Figure
  src="/images/deep-dives/typhoon-haiyan-2013.jpg"
  alt="…"
  caption="…"
  credit="Photo: …, via Wikimedia Commons."
/>

// Tool detail panels (compact, beside illustration)
<Figure variant="inline" src="…" alt="…" credit="…" />

// Profile avatars
<Figure variant="avatar" src={images.team.author} alt="…" />
```

**Required:** meaningful `alt` on every figure.

**Required for third-party photos:** `credit` with license and source.

**Defaults:** `loading="lazy"`, `decoding="async"` (avatar may use `loading="eager"` above the fold).

## MDX articles

Use `<Figure>` for photos and screenshots — never bare `<img>` or markdown `![](…)`.

End with `<Sources>` listing the image among primary references when it is a cited asset.

## Visualizer reference photos

Attach photos through `ProcessStage.photo` in data; `ProcessCycle` renders them with `<Figure variant="inline" />`.

Pair reference photos with CrayonArt stage illustrations when both exist.

## Social / OG previews

Default share cards use dynamic OG (`/api/og`). Article-specific raster images stay in the page body, not as automatic OG art unless explicitly wired later.
